{"word":"ἀνθεκτέος","slug":"ἀνθεκτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνθεκτέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:ἀντέχω'><el>ἀντέχω</el></a> \n<p/><i>one must cleave to</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἀνθεκτέα</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/>"}]}